From Joe Zbiciak Subject Re Booting from B drive In C Roger Pao writes much discussion about switching and drives removed Another albeit strange option is using a program like II available via anonymous FTP at many major sites or FDFORMAT also available via anonymous FTP that allows you to format disks to or HD disks to along with many MANY other formats so you can DISKCOPY yes the broken MeSsy DOS DISKCOPY the disks onto disks or vice I use this techniques with NON DOS self booting game disks on my old Tandy and it Another program named Teledisk shareware available on many major BBS's will also make the weird format disks provided you have II or FDFormat Some disks that won't DISKCOPY properly can be readily Teledisk'd into the proper At least this is a software solution for a hardware BIOS deficiency eh Joseph Zbiciak Disclaimer If you believe any of this check your head Nuke the Whales